{{wikipedia|Rusk}}
==English==

===Etymology===
{{Sp.}}  or Portugese ''[[rosca]]'' a twist or roll of bread.

===Noun===

'''rusk'''
#A kind of light, soft bread made with yeast and eggs, often toasted or crisped in an oven; or, a kind of sweetened biscuit.

====Synonyms====
*[[Brussels biscuit]]
*[[twice-baked bread]]
*[[zwieback]]

